## Two threads of next work

### Thread 1: Module-scoped namespaces (language feature)

Status entry: module-namespaces (codex-status)

The self-hosted compiler has a flat namespace across all .codex files.
Functions in X86_64.codex collide with CSharpEmitterExpressions.codex
(emit-expr, emit-let, emit-binary, emit-name, emit-if, emit-comparison).
Currently worked around with cg- prefix.

Scope of work:
- Design module scoping rules (how Chapter/file maps to namespace)
- Update the reference compiler parser + name resolver
- Update the self-hosted compiler parser + name resolver
- Rename cg-emit-expr back to emit-expr etc. in X86_64.codex
- Rename cg-emit-sub-rsp-imm32 back to emit-sub-rsp-imm32
- Also fixes: emit-int-lit, emit-function, emit-prologue, emit-epilogue,
  emit-start, emit-all-defs (these happen to not collide today but will
  as more emitters are added)
- Full list of cg- prefixed names in X86_64.codex:
  cg-emit-expr, cg-emit-name, cg-emit-let, cg-emit-binary,
  cg-emit-binary-op, cg-emit-comparison, cg-emit-if, cg-emit-sub-rsp-imm32

