Then M3.5 (records), M3.6 (match), M3.7 (lists), M3.8 (TCO), M3.9 (closures).

## Key learnings (carry forward)

- CCE encoding: C# test code constructing IR must use CCE-encoded strings
  for function names that the codegen compares against hardcoded literals
  (e.g. "main" = "\u001a\u000f\u0011\u0012"). Local variable names can
  be plain Unicode since they're only compared against themselves.
- No comments in Codex. Ever. Prose is the explanation layer.
- Avoid inline if/then/else in arithmetic (emitter drops parens).
- Break large ++ chains and deeply nested lets into named helpers.
- Clean out/ of .codex files before running codex build.
- Bare-metal memory is 128MB (64 pages). HWM is 73MB at 248K source.
